post_text:
Dear Kindergarten families:
We hope you are having a great summer! We are looking forward to
starting another amazing school year with your Kindergarten student.
There are a lot of new and exciting things happening on the Kindergarten
side of the building. The new classroom addition which includes 4 new rooms,
3 of them being Kindergarten rooms, is set to be finished in mid-July. We
have added a few new faces to our Kindergarten team too! Our teachers
this year are: Mrs. Angie Reed, Mrs. Lexi King, and Mrs. Tabitha Bartels.
We couldn’t be more excited to have them teaching your Kindergarten kiddo!
Please remember to contact the office (320) 594-2272 if you are in
need of paperwork or if you have any questions. More information will come
home soon about our Kinder Camp day. We are looking forward to another
awesome school year and cannot wait to meet this new group of Kinder Kids!
Class
of 2033

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school
meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to
purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text:
Starting Tuesday, May 19 through Friday, May 22 Browerville Public Schools will begin to collect text books, school-issued supplies, and Chromebooks. You may bring school-issued supplies to the school during regular school hours if the bus does not drive past your home, if you live in the city of Browerville, or if it does not work to meet the bus in the morning. School items can be returned using the morning bus route that goes by the vast majority of student homes. If possible, please group items together in a box.

When returning the Chromebook, place a piece of paper in the Chromebook with the student’s name and grade written on it if the Chromebook case is not labeled. Also make sure the charging cord is in the pocket of the Chromebook case. The cost of a missing charger is $15, and the cost of a cracked screen is $30.

post_text: This morning the Minnesota Department of Education along with the Minnesota Department of Health released new information regarding graduation ceremonies. The guidance basically bans in-person gatherings. With that information, the commencement ceremony scheduled for May 17 has been postponed. The district is currently working on an alternative. We will relay this information once we have all the details. We fully understand all the frustration you are experiencing as we continue on this uncontrollable path. Thank you for your patience.

COACH BUS TO XCEL ENERGY CENTER
STATE TEAM WRESTLING TOURNAMENT
• COST WILL BE $25.00 PER SEAT
• MAKE CHECK OUT TO : LPGE HIGH SCHOOL
• NEED 50 PEOPLE TO HAVE BUS
• FIRST 56 PEOPLE SIGNED UP WILL BE GUARANTEED A SPOT
• WILL TAKE MORE SIGN UPS AFTER FIRST 56, BUT THEN NEED ADDITIONAL 45 PEOPLE TO ADD A SECOND BUS.
• TICKET TO WRESTLING IS NOT INCLUDED! You must purchase your ticket at Xcel center or in advanced from either school
• Coach bus will leave Browerville bus turnaround at 5:10 am sharp. It will not wait for any reason, it will leave at 5:10 sharp
• Bus will then head to LPGE H.S. pick up there and head out at 5:30 sharp. It will not wait for any reason. It will leave at 5:30 from the front of the LPGE H.S.
• THE BUS WILL NOT STOP ON WAY DOWN OR THE WAY BACK

You must pay in advance when you sign up. Any Elem. student MUST be accompanied by/with an adult. (out of high school)

Fundraiser for Toys for Kids

*Sponsored by NHS

*Toys for Kids is a local program which helps support families in need during the holiday season. In the past over 200 kids in Todd county received gifts from this program. Your donation will help others have a Merry Christmas!

* Goal of $900 raised to help children in need have a great Christmas

*Dance on Friday, December 6, 7-10 PM

for students grades 7-12 – cost $3 purchased ticket ahead or $5 at door

*Other $ donations happily accepted

*If we exceed our goal students get an activity/movie time

during the morning of December 20

post_text: NHS held a fundraiser for the Browerville Area Foodshlef rasing $619.00. 8 faculty members had to kiss a goat, thank you to all who donated.
text: NHS held a fundraiser for the Browerville Area Foodshlef rasing $619.00. 8 faculty members had to kiss a goat, thank you to all who donated.

post_text:
This is an NHS Food Shelf Announcement

Would you like to see a teacher kiss a goat? How about 8 teachers? NHS members will be around collecting money for the Browerville Area Food Shelf this week. If we can raise $600 or more everyone will celebrate with ice cream. If there is $75 or more in each of these teachers envelopes they will kiss a goat at a student assembly next week. Donate to see Mr. Evenson, Mr. Stier, Mr. Peterson, Mr. Doss, Mrs. Emery, Mrs. Irsfeld, Mrs. Eckel, and Ms. Werder kiss a goat! Every dollar counts! Thank you.

BHS Musical Auditions for
“The Addams Family”
will be held
Wednesday, September 4
Thursday, September 5
Friday, September 6

Audition times are:
7:00 AM – 8:00 AM
3:30 PM – 5:00 PM

Auditions will be held in the music room.
Must be in grades 7-12 to audition.
Audition forms will be outside the music room.
Please fill out the form and bring it to your audition.

If you are interested in being a part of the musical, but do not want to be on stage, here is a list of other opportunities to be involved.

• Costume, hair, and make-up
• Lights and sound
• Publicity (making posters and getting the word out about the show)
• Set design and construction

For more information about the musical, please feel free to contact Miss Granby at bgranby@browerville.k12.mn.us
OR
Stop by the Music Room during the Open House on Wednesday, August 28 from 6 – 7 PM.
